Hi,

Here is the step to have the mobile phone signed with IMEI.

As advised by gpsunderground, sign on to www.symbiansigned.com

go to this link https://www.symbiansigned.com/app/page/overview/latestProductUpdates
to donwload DevCertRequest and install it in your PC

Open the installed program "Symbian Developer Certificate Request" and follow steps and generate... select the required capabilities in step 4.

Once the *.csr is generated go to
https://www.symbiansigned.com/app/barclayhtml/devcert/requestupload.jsp

follow the steps..

wait for the page to load with your DevCert and download the same to your PC

Install it in your Nokia 95 and proceed installing the downloaded route66 application...

Hope it helps guys.

for more easy tutorial please visit:
http://www.gosymbian.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=757

I cannot understand why so many idiots are still asking others to sign SIS files - get a grip of yourselves, go to 
https://www.symbiansigned.com/app/page

http://www.2ip.com/signup.php
Then head to 
https://www.symbiansigned.com/app/page/public/openSignedOnline.do
LOGIN, then look down that page until you see a box where you put your phones IMEI, your newly made email address and point symbian to your SIS file for signing, if you dont see the word SUCCESS at the top of the page after uploading your SIS file, you fucked up, try again!.....when you've got that right, move on, read everything, follow all the prompts - its easy, if you fail in the end, stick a feather up your arse and do the funky chicken!
